	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=108660><span id= >Theraun</span></a><br><span id=notbold>47 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.11]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Let's see, <br>/em checks his money bag....hhhmm about 90pp, that at lvl 39:)<br><br>I don't think anyone has bunches of money except druids, wizzies, and people who have played forever.<br><br>The trick is to find things that will make you more money, or let you spend less.<br><br>ex. when i was of the lvl to hunt wisps I sold all my greater light stones to a vendor for 3pp and change..thought I was rich:) I could have saved them up, ran to N. Karana and given them to the gypsy women for a research book, sold the research book for 9pp:)<br><br>Learn all the things that will make you money and do it.<br><br>2)use that spell that summons food and water...It will save you tons of money in the long run. I didn't until I was lvl 30:( Duh.. I was saving money by not buying the spell..<br><br>3) Don't be to proud to take donations from high lvl people for things like bind. Don't ask for donations, or shout binding for donations, but if they offer, take it. Give all newbies/low lvls a break though as they are poor like you! High level people will know you are a cleric and poor and often donate for simple stuff like a bind.<br><br>4)Don't give out the symbol buff to everyone in your group. only the fighters, yourself, maybe the chanter.(ignore this one if you're in a dungeon, buff everyone with everything in a dungeon). I know this sounds stingy, but I've tried it both ways and it makes no difference 90% of the time in outdoor zones. <br><br>5) When buying equipment, research the prices first. A LOT of people sell stuff for more than it's worth. Most people auction at the highest fair price, ALWAYS offer less.(quite a bit less, they will come back with a counter offer). If you can't get what you want.. WAIT.. it will come up in a day or two.<br><br>6)Research some items that you can camp for..wait until you are a couple of lvls over the lvl to obtain it.. then go camp it. I did this with the Iksar Berserkers Club. It took a week. I got no experience during that week. I died a couple of times. I got the club and sold it for 900pp plus about 600pp in trade items. Then I could buy gear.<br><br>7) Get in a guild, make them go to dungeons with you to get exp and good loot. the loot (pp and drop items are always better in dungeons).<br><br><br>Thats all I know:) I Ignore my own lessons a lot of the time(especiall on buffs and taking donations). Decide for yourself!<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Cortte Gesture<br>Un-retired / still gimp cleric<br>Kortte Jester<br>Shaman/Bear<br>Vazaelle<br><br><br></td></tr>
